<br />Sprite 0 hit will not occur. Why does rendering need to be turned off during the top portion of the screen and have a sprite-based status bar instead? Since Sprite rendering is turned on I assume the sprite overflow bit will still work so I guess you could use that. I doubt any emulators authors would've ignored to add something as simple as that so it should be well emulaed.</div>

